##Temperature at the border, daily visits to more than 40 prisoners: Disease does not delay my work

NVHAIBIEPA

Function introduction, for Chinese women's safety, to provide professional solutions.

Hi, I'm Tian Jing.

According to the regulations, today is the third working day after the Spring Festival, and I still stay at home to deal with my work. I thought a lot of people would be like me, but here's the thing: a lot of people are risking their lives to get out of their homes and back to work.

Thousands of miles away from the center of the outbreak of china-vietnam border, Zhang Yang returned to the unit after passing four checkpoints.

It's not the border you think it is. Barbed wire, border guards. It is a lively trade exchange between China and Vietnam.

In previous years, Zhang Yang would have been in a crowded market, listening to the soft cries of Vietnamese vendors, tasting delicious Vietnamese snacks, and shopping for cheap and exotic products.

As soon as this year's epidemic comes, if facing the enemy, the market will be closed down. grass-roots workers and Border Police will be stationed on the highways and set up checkpoints.

There was also a doctor who had applied to return to work, and her patient was a prisoner of the prison.

They say prison is the safest place to be right now. But because of the outbreak, she now sees more than 40 inmates a day, and every one of them gets hotter and more nervous than usual.

"We should treat the enemy with strategic contempt and the enemy with tactical importance, " she said

The epidemic affected all walks of life, the financial industry is not immune, securities company Yuan Li, looking at the opening of the New Year electronic screen: Are All Green, when can a red?

Across the screen, I seem to be in this sentence, saw her dewy eyes, Quirky and full of sadness.

In the event of disaster, these ordinary individuals who hold on to their posts are our hope.

As Zhang Yang said, "it's spring, it's going to be fine! "

China-vietnam border

Always on the Hook Hook Hook Hook for three days in a field

In an era of globalization, population movements are faster and more intense than ever, and remote towns along the sino-vietnamese border are not going to sit idly by.

The day before work, Zhang Yang drove his red car south from the state capital of 文山, the Zhuang Autonomous Prefecture in Yunnan Province, through four checkpoints, and finally reached the Sino Vietnamese border.

"We were stopped more than 10 kilometres down the path and turned back to the main road, where we had to take temperature, register vehicles and personal information at each checkpoint, including where we lived and worked. "

A few years ago, after passing the public service exam, Zhang Yang entered the integrated agricultural service center in a town in Wenshan Zhuang and Miao Autonomous Prefecture. At the end of last year I bought a house in the state capital and got married. "I've stayed here all my life. "

In the grass-roots epidemic prevention and control, there is no delay in the work of the argument.

Although Zhang Yang's unit is located in a town, but the area is not small. The border between China and Vietnam in the township area is 108 kilometers long and there are 18 village committees (communities) , six of which border Vietnam.

In order to promote exchanges between the two countries, the government has set up five border trading points here. Market Day, the border exchange point became the local people and Vietnamese business contacts the best place, lively.

Now affected by the epidemic, border trading points are all closed, the two peoples have been blocked in their respective borders. The town's bazaar was closed, leaving behind a wet market, a hotel and two supermarkets.

"food markets are disinfected every day, hotels are quarantined for people with fever, and people entering supermarkets must wear masks, take their temperature and pay online as much as possible. "

The epidemic has disrupted the usual working state, grass-roots workers all return to the team, put into the fight against the epidemic work. Zhang Yang's colleagues have set up checkpoints between towns and villages to prevent the movement of people and affect the prevention and control of the epidemic.

"Some checkpoints operate on four shifts, some on three shifts, 24 hours a day. " Checkpoint workers include government employees, doctors, nurses and police officers at police stations, as well as border police along the border.

"people from the government, the hospital and the police station were gathered together to form four sub-units, and 18 sub-units from each village took turns to be on duty. "

Every staff member has to have his temperature taken every morning and afternoon.

Checkpoints bring about a lot of helplessness, but this is the current epidemic prevention and control of one of the most effective way.

On the first day of the blockade, villagers from another county went fishing by the river and were stopped between two checkpoints for three days in the wild.

Fortunately, the checkpoint staff found them at the end of their shift and escorted them out of the precinct in a car. Others are stranded on the mountain with their rvs.

The iron railings lay across the road and were impassable except for first-aid vehicles, emergency vehicles and vehicles carrying supplies.

Everyone has their own position on blocking cards, which is the most effective way to prevent and control the current epidemic at the national level and brings great inconvenience to life from the villagers'point of view.

The prevention and control of the epidemic in the frontier minority areas is different from that in the inland areas. The language is not well understood, the diploma is not high, the security consciousness is poor -- it seems to be the present situation of all the remote rural areas in China -- Foshan -- With it comes quarrels and helplessness.

The villagers had no access to it, and the team went from house to house in the village to take their temperature, two times a day, as if it was above 37.3 degrees, and the doctor went home to check for infection.

Arriving at work on February 2nd, Zhang Yang was given a respirator, but was not put into a lock lock lock lock lock Foshan -- he had cold symptoms and was therefore in the office on a day to day basis.

On 3 February, the first case was confirmed in Wenshan Zhuang and Miao Autonomous Prefecture, where the patient had visited a market frequented by Zhang Yang. Zhang Yang had to report his condition.

All workers are required to wear face masks, but protective equipment is still in short supply. "The supplies will be taken care of. "

"It's spring, it's going to be fine! " Zhang Yang said.

Literary and artistic workers

Something both times a person may cough and become disconcerted

On Feb. 3, she got up early, packed up, and hopped on an electric bike to Florida, because the subway system was off -- she had to change her ticket to get back to work.

Since the Spring Festival holiday, Haitian has been struggling to go home to see their parents. A year do not go home, the heart is always concerned about thousands of miles away from the parents, but the daily growth of the epidemic data make Haitian sob.

After much thought, the sea and sky finally chose to go home. Her husband dropped her off at the high-speed rail station on the outskirts of the city. It was already January 26, the second day of the first lunar month, the country has already launched a multi-level response.

Fortunately, in addition to Hubei, there are not many provinces road closure, the normal operation of the train. "Most of the passengers on the trains were wearing face masks, there were fewer people in the railway stations than usual, and staff were taking body temperature. "

My parents drove to the train station and sprayed it with alcohol over and over before they let Haitian on board.

Haitian is a literary and artistic workers, usually heavy performing tasks, basic no holidays. While most people travel and shop on May Day and the 11th, they still need to take part in performances.

Under comprehensive consideration, the unit was approved in mid-january after the notice: Spring Festival holiday from January 23 to February 10.

Many things in the world seem to be coincidences. On January 29, the provincial government of the province where the Haitian unit is located issued a notice that, except for special industries, other enterprises and institutions will resume work no earlier than February 9 at 2400 hours.

Later, someone joked about the sea and sky: "Your unit is not in advance to know the information of the epidemic? "

Haitian bought a February 9 return ticket, scheduled to work on the 10th.

But life doesn't seem to be able to stand up to planning, especially at a time like this when you have to be led by the nose.

Two days later, the unit to call Haitian: February 3 early to work, to change her ticket to arrive at the unit on time.

As a literary and artistic worker, it doesn't seem necessary to go to work early. However, as a subordinate department of the provincial office, and the sea-sky unit of the same level of other units on February 3 normal work.

Many times, people can see others idle, but do not see others pay, two comparison will always feel unfair. But few understand that fairness does not mean treating all people as the same, but treating each individual's unique situation in an even-handed manner.

In short, because of some people's dissatisfaction, sea and sky units had to go to work early.

"So many people are at work, in advance also did not complain, but some uncomfortable. " Haitian at his own expense to change the ticket, and asked a friend to buy a mask.

But the epidemic has become more and more serious, all over the country began to close roads, sea and sky home did not survive. In desperation, she re-booked the ticket to the smooth road to the airport.

On Feb. 2, the day of her departure, her parents drove her to the airport, but she was stopped twice by health officials to take her temperature.

"everyone on the plane was wearing masks, but there were people coughing all the time and they were still in a panic. "

On the morning of February 3rd, the news sent the epidemic notification data in time -- a total of 2829 cases were confirmed, 17205 cases were confirmed, and 21558 were suspected.

The first working day after the Spring Festival this year, the sun is just right, but the streets are empty, shops closed, no one can be seen.

At 8:30, everyone from the executive office is at work. Unlike in the past, this year's start-up has been less lively.

"The unit adopted the way of shift work, one person to a day. " After the meeting, most people returned home, leaving only the office to handle the day-to-day work on duty staff.

Haitian and colleagues were given three protective masks each. "You have to wear a mask if you want to go to work. "

In fact, in such a day, the unit does not have much work to deal with, the original dozen people in the office, only four people.

For the sea, being in the office is like being at home; it's just a different place, as if it were still boring.

After the first day, she will take another day off and then go on duty.

Securities worker

Call on me the biggest impact has not been going out but the stock market has taken a dive

Unlike Haitian, Yuan Li came back to work on her own initiative.

As a securities industry practitioner, the first trading day after the Spring Festival has special meaning every year -- as a stock investor would like to get off to a good start, and generally so.

But this year, as a result of the outbreak, it is heading in the opposite direction -- Towards a 1000-share limit. February 3, a shares opened, Shanghai stock market opened sharply lower 8.42% , more than 3,000 stocks fell by the daily limit, a nearly 23-year record..

But that's to be expected. Not only for financial practitioners such as Yuan Li this, for every stockholder is no surprise.

Yuan Li is the company's salesman, the main work is to recommend financial products to customers, do some financial configuration.

It has been seven or eight years since she came to work in Yunnan from her hometown in Sichuan Province. Yuan Li has bought a house and settled down in Kunming, and seems to have become a native of Yunnan.

On Jan. 22, COVID-19 pneumonia had made headlines when yuan flew from Kunming to her hometown in Sichuan Province after a holiday.

"At that time there was a suspected case in Kunming, but there was none in my hometown, and no one was wearing a mask on the road. "

In an epidemic, the fear of the virus becomes a fear of the unknown, and any changes that occur in the body are frightening. "I went back to the hospital with a cold and the doctor told me to come back and take my medicine. "

After the Lunar New Year's Eve, the local government issued a notice not to go out, and the highway leading from Yuan's hometown to the Chengdu Shuangliu International Airport was closed.

However, Yuan Li still wants to return to work, took a lot of detours to finally arrive at the airport. "A lot of flights have been cancelled because of the outbreak, but mine has not been affected. "

On February 2, she returned to Kunming.

Like many provinces across the country, Yunnan Province has issued several circulars to prevent and control the outbreak, including one that specifically requires companies to return to work and schools to open no earlier than Feb. 9.

In the age of the Internet, the influence of geography on work is becoming less and less. Yuan Li's company requires department heads to be on duty as much as possible, and other staff can take the online office way.

The company is in the busiest part of Kunming, Florida, "the parking fee is too expensive" .

Yuan used to travel by public transport before the bus system shut down, but now the city seems to have stopped and she has to drive to work.

Kunming's winter is still the same sunny, the temperature remains at more than ten degrees. But the road is not congested, there is no anxiety, street lights are still on, but do not see the rush hour in the past. Yuan Li felt a chill.

In the meantime, the company handles lunch. Staff on duty when entering the door to each disinfection, temperature.

Yuan Li is not a supervisor, according to the company's regulations, do not need to so early on duty.

"mainly I'm lazy. Too much work-related stuff is in the office. And there are a lot of clients and a lot of positions. "

These days, her most urgent is to stop the loss, can reduce the loss, must reduce. "sell the stocks you can, but anticipate the losses you can't. "

"The biggest impact on me wasn't going out, it was the stock market. " Over the past 2019, "cold winter" has become a high-frequency vocabulary: "Cold Winter of film and Television" , "cold winter of the Internet" , "cold winter of capital" ..

The outbreak of the epidemic, although the stock plunge is expected, but also inevitable melancholy. "thousand shares fall limit" means that the customer's capital evaporated, perhaps hidden in the stock, but how also can not find.

Financial people believe that the money how to go on how to go, although some one-sided, but also eased the panic of Yuan Li. "The economic data are telling us that the long term is good, but it's going to be difficult in January and the market is changing day by day. "

"saw a piece of green, when can a piece of red? " Yuan Li says, this is her first working day of this year the only idea.

"Life goes on. It depends on the sky. "

Prison doctor

・ ADVANCE THE CLOSURE OF DUTY to return to duty, daily consultations with more than 40 criminals

It is well known that prisons are very densely populated places and the consequences of an outbreak are unimaginable.

Because of the epidemic, the Kunming prison in Yunnan required some staff to return to work ahead of schedule. As a doctor in the prison hospital, Liu Ting, upon receiving the order, volunteered to be on duty to let the older colleagues have more rest for a few days.

In the days when stars disappeared from search engines, doctors took center stage. In this race against time, the only thing that might reassure everyone is the word "doctor. ".

At the start of the epidemic, the prison stopped meeting with prisoners and relatives. A temperature monitoring point has been set up at the entrance of the supervision area. Every person who enters the supervision area must have a temperature monitoring.

Liuting in accordance with the requirements of the end of the test, turned into the work.

As a double police family, Liu Ting husband is also on duty in the unit, the original lively home left only parents. Big New Year's, can not accompany in the parents side, do the daughter's heart of course very guilty.

Fortunately, her father supported her decision and, while on duty, brought her a note which read:

"Liu Ting, my son: your ability to stand up in the face of difficulties is enough to prove that you have lived up to what your father taught you. You must always be a qualified party member and live up to the trust placed in you by the prison. "

Public opinion likes to create God, especially in the confusion and panic at the moment. In fact, there is no white angel, but are the eyes of the parents of children, children eyes of parents.

Although parents understand, also support, but their hearts always feel indebted to them, and so win this epidemic prevention and control, Liu Ting ready to eat a lively reunion dinner.

As a result of the weather change, the common cold attack sharp increase, since the close duty, Liu Ting receives the disease to attack 40 on average every day.

Although the patients and the outside world has been closely isolated, there is no relevant contact history in Wuhan, but liuting still have to carefully inquire about the physical condition of the patients with fever.

"WHERE IS UNWELL? " , "what symptom is there? Is there aching and weakness in the limbs? " , "take your temperature first... " these words, every day to say dozens of times.

Ask Her if she's afraid of having so many fever patients every day? She replied with a smile: Strategically Despise the enemy, tactically value the enemy.

While the outbreak was kept strictly outside the prison walls, there were some more urgent situations during the watch, such as a prisoner who suddenly had severe abdominal pain and needed to be seen in an emergency room.

All the hospital quickly ready to receive, the patient arrived, through B ultrasound, x-ray examination, doctors for consultation, the initial diagnosis of suspected hollow organ perforation or intussusception May, life-threatening!

Under the guidance of the Central Hospital, we work together to complete the emergency response, 3:00 am criminals only slightly better, and the director of the whole night.

There was also a prisoner who had a sudden onset of hypertension and arrived at the hospital in a state of confusion. Due to high blood pressure, possible cerebral hemorrhage or cerebral infarction, the hospital did not have the conditions for treatment after rescue, and the colleagues had to be sent to the Central Hospital overnight.

It's all part of the day-to-day work of the Prison Hospital's medical staff. One might ask, why stay in a hospital like this, when it's hard to have a reputation without money.

The documentary "200 years of surgery" said: Medicine is a kind of expression of human emotions, it originated in the most simple human desire to help.

Doctors only see patients, no professional status, high and low.

Because the prison is closed management, relatively speaking, to be more flexible, all kinds of supplies are normal.

But the epidemic or to everyone taut string, weak criminals, specially issued a cotton-padded clothes quilt, do a good job of cold and warm to prevent colds, but also to strengthen the focus of disinfection and cleaning work.

Someone on the Internet joked that prison is the safest place right now. For Liu Ting, this is not a joke.

It's not just Liu Ting. After the epidemic, people may again forget the sacrifices of these medical workers. But disease does not forget people. It can happen at any time.

I think we need to remember something about medicine, not just forget it.

Two days later, the unit to call Haitian: February 3 early to work, to change her ticket to arrive at the unit on time.

As a literary and artistic worker, it doesn't seem necessary to go to work early. However, as a subordinate department of the provincial office, and the sea-sky unit of the same level of other units on February 3 normal work.

Literary and artistic workers

Something both times a person may cough and become disconcerted

On Feb. 3, she got up early, packed up, and hopped on an electric bike to Florida, because the subway system was off -- she had to change her ticket to get back to work.

Since the Spring Festival holiday, Haitian has been struggling to go home to see their parents. A year do not go home, the heart is always concerned about thousands of miles away from the parents, but the daily growth of the epidemic data make Haitian sob.

After much thought, the sea and sky finally chose to go home. Her husband dropped her off at the high-speed rail station on the outskirts of the city. It was already January 26, the second day of the first lunar month, the country has already launched a multi-level response.

Fortunately, in addition to Hubei, there are not many provinces road closure, the normal operation of the train. "Most of the passengers on the trains were wearing face masks, there were fewer people in the railway stations than usual, and staff were taking body temperature. "

My parents drove to the train station and sprayed it with alcohol over and over before they let Haitian on board.

Haitian is a literary and artistic workers, usually heavy performing tasks, basic no holidays. While most people travel and shop on May Day and the 11th, they still need to take part in performances.

Under comprehensive consideration, the unit was approved in mid-january after the notice: Spring Festival holiday from January 23 to February 10.

Many things in the world seem to be coincidences. On January 29, the provincial government of the province where the Haitian unit is located issued a notice that, except for special industries, other enterprises and institutions will resume work no earlier than February 9 at 2400 hours.

Later, someone joked about the sea and sky: "Your unit is not in advance to know the information of the epidemic? "

Haitian bought a February 9 return ticket, scheduled to work on the 10th.

But life doesn't seem to be able to stand up to planning, especially at a time like this when you have to be led by the nose.

As a literary and artistic worker, it doesn't seem necessary to go to work early. However, as a subordinate department of the provincial office, and the sea-sky unit of the same level of other units on February 3 normal work.

Many times, people can see others idle, but do not see others pay, two comparison will always feel unfair. But few understand that fairness does not mean treating all people as the same, but treating each individual's unique situation in an even-handed manner.

In short, because of some people's dissatisfaction, sea and sky units had to go to work early.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"So many people are at work, in advance also did not complain, but some uncomfortable. " Haitian at his own expense to change the ticket, and asked a friend to buy a mask.

But the epidemic has become more and more serious, all over the country began to close roads, sea and sky home did not survive. In desperation, she re-booked the ticket to the smooth road to the airport.

On Feb. 2, the day of her departure, her parents drove her to the airport, but she was stopped twice by health officials to take her temperature.

"everyone on the plane was wearing masks, but there were people coughing all the time and they were still in a panic. "

On the morning of February 3rd, the news sent the epidemic notification data in time -- a total of 2829 cases were confirmed, 17205 cases were confirmed, and 21558 were suspected.

The first working day after the Spring Festival this year, the sun is just right, but the streets are empty, shops closed, no one can be seen.

At 8:30, everyone from the executive office is at work. Unlike in the past, this year's start-up has been less lively.

"The unit adopted the way of shift work, one person to a day. " After the meeting, most people returned home, leaving only the office to handle the day-to-day work on duty staff.

Haitian and colleagues were given three protective masks each. "You have to wear a mask if you want to go to work. "

In fact, in such a day, the unit does not have much work to deal with, the original dozen people in the office, only four people.

For the sea, being in the office is like being at home; it's just a different place, as if it were still boring.

After the first day, she will take another day off and then go on duty.

Securities worker

Call on me the biggest impact has not been going out but the stock market has taken a dive

Unlike Haitian, Yuan Li came back to work on her own initiative.

As a securities industry practitioner, the first trading day after the Spring Festival has special meaning every year -- as a stock investor would like to get off to a good start, and generally so.

But this year, as a result of the outbreak, it is heading in the opposite direction -- Towards a 1000-share limit. February 3, a shares opened, Shanghai stock market opened sharply lower 8.42% , more than 3,000 stocks fell by the daily limit, a nearly 23-year record..

But that's to be expected. Not only for financial practitioners such as Yuan Li this, for every stockholder is no surprise.

Yuan Li is the company's salesman, the main work is to recommend financial products to customers, do some financial configuration.

It has been seven or eight years since she came to work in Yunnan from her hometown in Sichuan Province. Yuan Li has bought a house and settled down in Kunming, and seems to have become a native of Yunnan.

On Jan. 22, COVID-19 pneumonia had made headlines when yuan flew from Kunming to her hometown in Sichuan Province after a holiday.

"At that time there was a suspected case in Kunming, but there was none in my hometown, and no one was wearing a mask on the road. "

In an epidemic, the fear of the virus becomes a fear of the unknown, and any changes that occur in the body are frightening. "I went back to the hospital with a cold and the doctor told me to come back and take my medicine. "

After the Lunar New Year's Eve, the local government issued a notice not to go out, and the highway leading from Yuan's hometown to the Chengdu Shuangliu International Airport was closed.

However, Yuan Li still wants to return to work, took a lot of detours to finally arrive at the airport. "A lot of flights have been cancelled because of the outbreak, but mine has not been affected. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 2, she returned to Kunming.

Like many provinces across the country, Yunnan Province has issued several circulars to prevent and control the outbreak, including one that specifically requires companies to return to work and schools to open no earlier than Feb. 9.

In the age of the Internet, the influence of geography on work is becoming less and less. Yuan Li's company requires department heads to be on duty as much as possible, and other staff can take the online office way.

The company is in the busiest part of Kunming, Florida, "the parking fee is too expensive" .

Yuan used to travel by public transport before the bus system shut down, but now the city seems to have stopped and she has to drive to work.

Kunming's winter is still the same sunny, the temperature remains at more than ten degrees. But the road is not congested, there is no anxiety, street lights are still on, but do not see the rush hour in the past. Yuan Li felt a chill.

In the meantime, the company handles lunch. Staff on duty when entering the door to each disinfection, temperature.

Yuan Li is not a supervisor, according to the company's regulations, do not need to so early on duty.

"mainly I'm lazy. Too much work-related stuff is in the office. And there are a lot of clients and a lot of positions. "

These days, her most urgent is to stop the loss, can reduce the loss, must reduce. "sell the stocks you can, but anticipate the losses you can't. "

"The biggest impact on me wasn't going out, it was the stock market. " Over the past 2019, "cold winter" has become a high-frequency vocabulary: "Cold Winter of film and Television" , "cold winter of the Internet" , "cold winter of capital" ..

The outbreak of the epidemic, although the stock plunge is expected, but also inevitable melancholy. "thousand shares fall limit" means that the customer's capital evaporated, perhaps hidden in the stock, but how also can not find.

Financial people believe that the money how to go on how to go, although some one-sided, but also eased the panic of Yuan Li. "The economic data are telling us that the long term is good, but it's going to be difficult in January and the market is changing day by day. "

"saw a piece of green, when can a piece of red? " Yuan Li says, this is her first working day of this year the only idea.

"Life goes on. It depends on the sky. "

Prison doctor

・ ADVANCE THE CLOSURE OF DUTY to return to duty, daily consultations with more than 40 criminals

It is well known that prisons are very densely populated places and the consequences of an outbreak are unimaginable.

Because of the epidemic, the Kunming prison in Yunnan required some staff to return to work ahead of schedule. As a doctor in the prison hospital, Liu Ting, upon receiving the order, volunteered to be on duty to let the older colleagues have more rest for a few days.

In the days when stars disappeared from search engines, doctors took center stage. In this race against time, the only thing that might reassure everyone is the word "doctor. ".

At the start of the epidemic, the prison stopped meeting with prisoners and relatives. A temperature monitoring point has been set up at the entrance of the supervision area. Every person who enters the supervision area must have a temperature monitoring.

Liuting in accordance with the requirements of the end of the test, turned into the work.

As a double police family, Liu Ting husband is also on duty in the unit, the original lively home left only parents. Big New Year's, can not accompany in the parents side, do the daughter's heart of course very guilty.

Fortunately, her father supported her decision and, while on duty, brought her a note which read:

"Liu Ting, my son: your ability to stand up in the face of difficulties is enough to prove that you have lived up to what your father taught you. You must always be a qualified party member and live up to the trust placed in you by the prison. "

Public opinion likes to create God, especially in the confusion and panic at the moment. In fact, there is no white angel, but are the eyes of the parents of children, children eyes of parents.

Although parents understand, also support, but their hearts always feel indebted to them, and so win this epidemic prevention and control, Liu Ting ready to eat a lively reunion dinner.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As a result of the weather change, the common cold attack sharp increase, since the close duty, Liu Ting receives the disease to attack 40 on average every day.

Although the patients and the outside world has been closely isolated, there is no relevant contact history in Wuhan, but liuting still have to carefully inquire about the physical condition of the patients with fever.

"WHERE IS UNWELL? " , "what symptom is there? Is there aching and weakness in the limbs? " , "take your temperature first... " these words, every day to say dozens of times.

Ask Her if she's afraid of having so many fever patients every day? She replied with a smile: Strategically Despise the enemy, tactically value the enemy.

While the outbreak was kept strictly outside the prison walls, there were some more urgent situations during the watch, such as a prisoner who suddenly had severe abdominal pain and needed to be seen in an emergency room.

All the hospital quickly ready to receive, the patient arrived, through B ultrasound, x-ray examination, doctors for consultation, the initial diagnosis of suspected hollow organ perforation or intussusception May, life-threatening!

Under the guidance of the Central Hospital, we work together to complete the emergency response, 3:00 am criminals only slightly better, and the director of the whole night.

There was also a prisoner who had a sudden onset of hypertension and arrived at the hospital in a state of confusion. Due to high blood pressure, possible cerebral hemorrhage or cerebral infarction, the hospital did not have the conditions for treatment after rescue, and the colleagues had to be sent to the Central Hospital overnight.

It's all part of the day-to-day work of the Prison Hospital's medical staff. One might ask, why stay in a hospital like this, when it's hard to have a reputation without money.

The documentary "200 years of surgery" said: Medicine is a kind of expression of human emotions, it originated in the most simple human desire to help.

Doctors only see patients, no professional status, high and low.

Because the prison is closed management, relatively speaking, to be more flexible, all kinds of supplies are normal.

But the epidemic or to everyone taut string, weak criminals, specially issued a cotton-padded clothes quilt, do a good job of cold and warm to prevent colds, but also to strengthen the focus of disinfection and cleaning work.

Someone on the Internet joked that prison is the safest place right now. For Liu Ting, this is not a joke.

It's not just Liu Ting. After the epidemic, people may again forget the sacrifices of these medical workers. But disease does not forget people. It can happen at any time.

I think we need to remember something about medicine, not just forget it.
